{
  "text": "While most mRNAs are efficiently exported, the export of long non-coding RNAs (lncRNAs) is generally less efficient, indicating that specific mechanisms can inhibit export and regulate nuclear RNA retention [CITATION_1] . Most of the known sequences that regulate nuclear RNA export in mammals were originally identified in viral genomes [CITATION_2] . Two new studies now use elegant tiling-based approaches to screen for cis-acting RNA elements involved in nuclear retention.",
